OL,5,FAt the time of D-Day she was with
OL,6,FFighter Command.
OL,8,FHer joy at the news of the invasion
OL,9,Fwas tempered by the fact that her
OL,10,Ffiance - a bomb aimer - had just been
OL,11,Fkilled when his Lancaster was shot
OL,12,Fdown during a raid.
OL,14,FShe said: "When my boyfriend was
OL,15,Fposted as missing I was living with
OL,16,Fhis parents. And of course it wasn't a
OL,17,Fhappy homecoming.
